RACE.FOOTNOTES: VANCOUGAR tracked three deep then three wide on the turn, bid four deep in upper stretch, took over with a furlong remaining and inched away from the runner-up. SINGLE TRACK MIND (IRE) stalked two wide into the turn, moved over to the rail around the bend, bid between rivals in upper stretch but got outkicked by the winner. BOLT SUPREMACY took a light bump from outside at the start, bumped with same rival crossing the dirt early, trailed into the turn, angled out and raced four deep into the lane, put in a late run and gained the show. ACQUIRED CLASS stalked on the inside into the turn, got put in tight along the rail around the bend, looked for room behind rivals in upper stretch, gained a clear path and kept on to earn a minor award. HABEAS set the pace under pressure from DON CORLEONE early, inched away from that rival into the turn, led along the rail into the stretch, lost command outside the eighth pole and weakened. DON CORLEONE showed early speed and pressure HABEAS in the early going, chased that rival in the two path through the turn and three deep in upper stretch, then weakened in the furlong grounds. YOGI BOY stumbled and bumped inner rival leaving the gate, bumped again crossing the dirt, ran up on heels up the backstretch, got boxed in on the turn, chased two wide into the drive, altered out from behind DON CORELONE in the stretch and was ridden out. SAN ANTON (IRE) was off slow to begin, traveled three wide outside foes on the bend and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEZMISBEHAVING was off slow to start, unhurried three wide early, lacked room at the three-eighths pole, rallied four wide into the stretch, drew alongside the top pair in the final furlong and drove clear. ASHLEYS SANDCASTLE brushed the gate, took back early and trailed inside, moved out in the middle stages, rallied four wide on the far turn, vied four deep with a quarter mile remaining, took a short lead while drifting in and bumping LOVE OUR FAMILY in upper stretch, lost command at the sixteenth pole and held the place. CANDY ON TOP broke well then settled in the two path outside a rival, found traffic on the far turn and steered to the inside, tipped out in upper stretch and finished willingly for the show. LOVE OUR FAMILY showed keen early foot then chased in the two path, moved up to apply pressure from outside, got bumped by DEL MAR WOMAN three times midway around the far turn, fought three deep late on the bend, got bumped from outside in upper stretch, battled to the sixteenth pole and faltered. ELEGANCE CODE stalked from inside early, launched a bid from the fence at the five-sixteenth pole, vied with outer rivals to the stretch and flattened in the lane. YVETT'S SURPRISE steadied and pulled hard early, settled inside off the pace, trailed while angling four wide leaving the far turn and could not threaten. TAPIT ROCKS pulled and steadied behind the top pair prior to the first turn, stalked between rivals early, outside a foe into the far turn, got blocked behind trouble rivals and checked at the quarter pole and could not rally once in the clear. DEL MAR WOMAN dueled early from inside then took control from LOVE OUR FAMILY, got pressured from that rival in the middle stages, drifted out and bumped repeatedly midway on the far turn and faded down the lane. CEE MINUS stalked three deep early on, raced in mid-pack outside a rival into the far turn, spun three wide into the lane and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE'S RESILIENT broke out a bit to bother CORNELIA FORT, showed speed from inside to take the front with NIGHT PARTY to the outside, inched away on the turn, shifted two wide into the stretch and was challenged by HIALEASH HOTTIE, lugged out from the left hand in upper stretch, switched to right-handed urging in the final furlong while holding a short lead and gamely prevailed. HIALEAH HOTTIE chased three deep early, bid three wide into the stretch, got floated out by SHE'S RESILIENT in upper stretch, stayed on gamely through furlong grounds but could not get by. CORNELIA FORT broke a step slow and was bothered from inside, chased outside a rival at the back into the turn, angled in while inching closer around the bend and showed a mild response to earn the show honors. THE REIGN SONG settled on the inside, got boxed in entering the turn, lost ground and had to angle out around the bend, came four wide into the drive and kept on to improve position. NIGHT PARTY raced up close then applied pressure to the outside. IT'S SAUL RIGHT was off a bit slow in the beginning, chased on the inside under coaxing around the bend, tipped two wide nearing the stretch and weakened. THERE WAS A RIDER'S CLAIM OF FOUL LODGED BY THE RIDER ABOARD HIALEAH HOTTIE AGAINST SHE'S RESILIENT ALLEGING INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH. THERE WAS ALSO A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INOVLING THE SAME MATTER AND AFTER A REVIEW RULED THAT ALTHOUGH SHE'S RESILIENT DID LUG OUT IN UPPER STRETCH IT DID NOT COST HILEAH HOTTIE A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING.

By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, March 16, 2023, closed with 17 or by Supplementary nomination of $2,000 due at time of entry. $750 to enter and an additional $750 to start with $100,00 0 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth and $2,000 to fifth. Weight 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of A Race other than Maiden, Claiming or Starter allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAST AND SHINY set the pace outside TEENA ELLA early, cleared that rival and crossed over to the inside into the turn, came off the rail crossing the dirt and showed the way into the lane, put to right-handed urging in upper stretch and held well over the runner-up. TEENA ELLA pressed from inside early then ceded command nearing the turn, shifted to the two path to give chase from outside, came out crossing the dirt, took aim in the final furlong, drew alongside FAST AND SHINY late but ran out of time. MANHATTAN JUNGLE (IRE) was off alertly from inside, stalked the top pair early, traveled two wide around the turn, had to alter out from behind TEENA ELLA crossing the dirt, continued to give chase within range into the final furlong, could not summon the needed late kick and held the show. BROADWAY GIRLS tracked from inside around the turn, drifted out crossing surfaces and failed to respond when called upon. RAGTIME ROSE settled off the pace, rounded the bend two to three wide, drifted out over the dirt and could not rally. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY AND AFTER A REVIEW RULED THAT ALTHOUGH TEENA ELLA DUCKED OUT CROSSING THE DIRT IT DID NOT COST MANHATTAN JUNGLE (IRE) A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING. HALF-MILE FRACTION HAND-TIMED.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KRISTI'S TIGER settled off the pace near the inside, tipped out and closed in on the leader on the turn, drew alongside and quickly took over at the quarter pole, kicked clear in upper stretch and remained comfortably in front to the wire. BOWL OF CHERRIES trailed early and moved off the rail, tipped four wide into the turn, remained wide into the stretch, finished determinedly in the drive, could not threaten the winner but was clearly second best. RACE.FOOTNOTES: THIRTY FOUR COUPE prominent early then allowed BELMONT BILL to take the front, switched to the outside leaving the first turn, took aim two wide into the stretch, drew alongside the leader and dueled down the lane, took over nearing the sixteenth pole and proved best in the end. BELMONT BILL showed speed outside a pair of rivals then cleared and crossed over early, kicked away from THIRTY FOUR COUPE on the backstretch, led clear through the far turn and into the stretch, met the challenge from THIRTY FOUR COUPE in the stretch and yielded grudgingly. UPRIGHT showed speed between rivals early then ceded command crossing the finish line for the first time, tucked inside on the first turn, saved ground to the stretch and finished willingly to regain the show honors. THE KEY IS UNITY got brushed from inside at the start, chased between rivals, three then two wide on the first turn, move inside on the backstretch, tipped two wide around the far turn, moved out further in the drive and got edged for the show. SHADOW CREEK (IRE) was reserved in the early going on the inside, stayed along the fence through the far turn, raced a bit off the rail into the drive, moved out in the stretch and failed to threaten. CHURCHMEISTER was a bit rank in the beginning while losing his path, trailed on the inside into the first turn, got blocked through the second turn, moved out to a clear path and kept on to improve placings. ANTICIPATED sat off the pace two wide early then between rivals, saved ground on the inside around the far turn and lacked a rally. DEEP RIVER brushed outer rival at the start, checked between rivals then pulled early in the three path, trailed four wide into the far turn, moved into the three path around that bend, angled out in the drive and failed to make an impact. TENTH STREET DON was off a bit slow in the beginning, chased three, four, then five wide around the first turn, chased four deep up the backstretch, came three wide into the lane, drifted in and failed to menace. DONTTESTYOURLUCK stumbled at the start, chased three to four wide off the pace, got blocked past the three-eighths pole, raced three deep at the quarter pole, two wide into the stretch and failed to rally. REIGN OVER ME pulled a bit when reserved near the inside, moved into the two path on the clubhouse turn, angled out to the five path around the second bend and was not a factor. TIZACRAFTYMINISTER climbed in the early stages, chased outside a rival into the far turn, started to climb again on the far turn and dropped back, then faded in the drive. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION THE THREE-QUARTER AND SEVEN-EIGHTHS FRACTIONS WERE HAND-TIMED.
